userTask.name: Select products
userTask.documentation: "If the login was successful then the customer can continue to select products, else [...]. After selecting a product the customer has to add it to a shopping cart, save the product and check if every product was already selected." I understood this part of the description as follows: First, the customer browses through all the products available and makes up his mind what he wants to buy. Then, to buy a product, he adds it to the cart and saves it. At last, he checks the cart for missing products, and in case something is missing, he adds that product. He does that until all products are in the cart. Therefore, the loop does not go back to the task 'Select products', since this is where the customer just browses the page only once, to get an overview of what he wants to purchase. Only the adding and saving products task, as well as the checking the cart for completeness are in the loop.
